# Code Review: `app.js`

The current file is minimal (23 lines) with no error handling or input validation. Here are concrete improvements focused on security best practices:

## Issues Found

### 1. No global error handling
An uncaught error in any handler will crash the process or leak stack traces to clients.

### 2. No request body parsing limits
If body-parsing middleware is added later without limits, the app is vulnerable to payload-based DoS.

### 3. Missing security headers
No `helmet` or equivalent — responses lack `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, CSP, etc.

### 4. No rate limiting
`/users` and `/health` can be abused for scraping / DoS.

### 5. `/users` has no input validation
Currently it takes no input, but any future filtering (e.g. `?id=`) would need validation.

### 6. `process.on` handlers missing
No `uncaughtException` / `unhandledRejection` handlers — silent failures or crash without logging.

### 7. Hardcoded port and no graceful shutdown
`SIGTERM` won't drain in-flight requests; port should come from env.

### 8. Server started on import
`app.listen` runs when the module is required (e.g., in tests), leaking a port.

---

## Suggested Rewrite

```js
const express = require('express');
const helmet = require('helmet');
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
const { z } = require('zod');

const app = express();

// Security headers
app.use(helmet());

// Body parser with strict size limit
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));

// Basic rate limiting
app.use(rateLimit({
  windowMs: 60_000,
  max: 100,
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
}));

app.get('/health', (_req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
});

// Example: validated query input with zod
const UsersQuery = z.object({
  limit: z.coerce.number().int().min(1).max(100).optional(),
});

app.get('/users', (req, res, next) => {
  const parsed = UsersQuery.safeParse(req.query);
  if (!parsed.success) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid query parameters' });
  }
  const users = [
    { id: 1, name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' },
    { id: 2, name: 'Bob', email: 'bob@example.com' },
  ];
  res.json(parsed.data.limit ? users.slice(0, parsed.data.limit) : users);
});

// 404 handler
app.use((_req, res) => res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }));

// Central error handler — never leak stack traces
// eslint-disable-next-line no-unused-vars
app.use((err, _req, res, _next) => {
  console.error('Unhandled error:', err);
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});

// Only listen when run directly, not when required by tests
if (require.main === module) {
  const port = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;
  const server = app.listen(port, () => {
    console.log(`Server running on port ${port}`);
  });

  const shutdown = (signal) => {
    console.log(`Received ${signal}, shutting down...`);
    server.close(() => process.exit(0));
    setTimeout(() => process.exit(1), 10_000).unref();
  };
  process.on('SIGTERM', () => shutdown('SIGTERM'));
  process.on('SIGINT', () => shutdown('SIGINT'));
  process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason) => {
    console.error('Unhandled rejection:', reason);
  });
  process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
    console.error('Uncaught exception:', err);
    shutdown('uncaughtException');
  });
}

module.exports = app;
```

---

## Priority Summary

| Priority | Change | Why |
|---|---|---|
| High | Central error handler + 404 handler | Prevents stack-trace leakage (OWASP A05) |
| High | `helmet` | Secure-by-default headers |
| High | `express.json({ limit })` | Mitigates DoS via large payloads |
| High | Input validation (zod/joi) on all user input | Prevents injection & malformed-input crashes |
| Medium | Rate limiting | Mitigates brute-force / scraping |
| Medium | Graceful shutdown + process-level handlers | Reliability & observability |
| Medium | `require.main === module` guard | Avoids side-effects in tests |
| Low | `PORT` from env | Twelve-factor config |

